name: Kislay
tweet: 16.Their delivery process & unmatchd efficiency hs bn the subject of FedEx,one of the biggest courier compnies in the world #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 15. From IIM-A to Harvard,their impeccable mngmnt skills hv bn studied nd analysed in top business schools around the world #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 14. Dabbawalas earn about Rs 12,000 a month. They do other odd jobs  after the 9 hours of ferrying tiffin boxes.  #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 13.The first time dabbawalas went on a strike was in 2011, to support Anna Hazare in his anti-corruption campaign. #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 12. One acknowledged mistake took place in 2005, wen Mumbai was lashed by heavy rains and a dabbawala was unable to deliver #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 11.The dabbawalas claimed that in their 120 years of operation, they've erred once in 16 million transactions. #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 10. The organization has earned a six-sigma rating, which means 1 error in 6 million transactions. #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 9. The dabbawala service is legendary for its reliability. Their service is uninterrupted even on days of extreme weather. #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 8. Each Dabbawal is not an employee but an entrepreneur and an equal shareholder in the Dabbawallah Trust. #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 7. Every dabbawalla receives the same income irrespective of age, experience and number of costumers served. #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 6. They have perfected  the art of timely, accurate delivery through a simple code system written on each dabba #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 5. Most dabbawalas are illiterate (8th graders)                               #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 4. 1 dabba changes hands at least 6 times in transit before it  reaches the consumer. #MumbaiDabbawala

name: Kislay
tweet: 3. 5000 odd dabbawalas deliver roughly 200000 'home-cooked' lunches each day, moving on bicycles, trains and on foot.  #MumbaiDabbawala

tweet: 2. Mahadeo Bhavaji Bachche, the first dabbawala, started delivering lunch to a Britisher at his request. #MumbaiDabbawala
